fr.apteryx.imageio.dicom
Class StorageCommitmentSCU

Object
  StorageCommitmentSCU

public class StorageCommitmentSCU
extends Object

Implements a Storage Commitment SCU. A Storage Commitment SCU is used to request from a peer SCP that it commits to safekeep SOP instances that it has previously received (typically using the Storage Service Class). When a StorageCommitmentSCU is instantiated, a StorageCommitmentResultReceiver must be specified. The StorageCommitmentResultReceiver determines the listener that will be called when the result for a request is received from the SCP. The SCP can send the result either within the association the SCU used to send the request, or within a new association initiated by the SCP. If the SCU must be able to receive such new association, the StorageCommitmentResultReceiver must be started before a Storage Commitment Request is sent.

If the persistent argument of the constructor is set to false, the request is sent in an association that is initiated and released when sendRequest is called and no result can be received in this association. If persistent is set to true, the association is established in the constructor and the close method must be called to manually release the association. This setting allows to send multiple requests in the same association and gives the SCP the opportunity to send the result in this association.

An arbritrary amount of time may pass between the request is sent and the result is received, depending on the way the SOP instances were transmitted (across the network, on physical media, etc.), and the operations needed by the SCP to ensure safekeeping of the instances.

Also see StorageSCU.storeAndRequestCommitment for an easy usage of this service class.

Constructor Detail

StorageCommitmentSCU

public StorageCommitmentSCU(PeerAE peer,
                            StorageCommitmentResultReceiver scrr,
                            boolean persistent)
Creates a new Storage Commitment SCU that will send requests to peer and use scrr to receive the result. This constructor establishes the association with the SCP if persistent is true.

The result may be sent by the SCP either in this association, if persistent is true, or in a new association initiated by the SCP. In order to be able to receive the result in an association initiated by the SCP, scrr must have been created using the proper network information (port, IP adress, secure transport), and started using its start method before the request is sent.

In both cases, scrr.resultReceived is called by the plugin when the result is received.

Method Detail

sendRequest

public void sendRequest(StorageCommitmentSCU.Request req)
                 throws DicomException,
                        IOException,
                        InterruptedException
Sends a request for storage commitment to the SCP. The SOP instances the SCP is asked to safekeep are defined by req.

If this instance was created with a persistent association, this association is used, else a new association is established and released in this method.

DicomException

close

public void close()
           throws IOException
Closes the persistent association. This method must be called only if this instance was created with a persistent association. This SCU cannot be used to send requests after this method has been called.

Throws:
